The code of this notebook is mainly borrowed from the script demo.lua from the GitHub repository of the authors https://github.com/pathak22/context-encoder. It produces images to visualize the filters of some (convolutional) layers of the networks, visualization of the activations at various depths after forwarding through an image and finally saving in a csv file (https://github.com/clementfarabet/lua---csv) the hidden 4000 features between the encoder and the decoder that we subsequently use for visualization in a separate ipython notebook (more familiar with python for this kind of work): features_reduction.ipynb.

To run this notebook please visit and clone https://github.com/pathak22/context-encoder, you need to download the model(s). The input images that we use in this notebook and the other notebooks are from the datasets mentionned in our review.

Test¶

require 'nn'
require 'image'

torch.setdefaulttensortype('torch.FloatTensor')
net = torch.load('models/inpaintCenter/imagenet_inpaintCenter.t7')

opt = {
    batchSize = 1,        -- number of samples to produce
    net = 'models/inpaintCenter/imagenet_inpaintCenter.t7',              -- path to the generator network
    imDir = 'images/tp2',            -- directory containing pred_center
    name = 'demo_out',     -- name of the file saved
    gpu = 0,               -- gpu mode. 0 = CPU, 1 = 1st GPU etc.
    nc = 3,                -- # of channels in input
    manualSeed = 222,        -- 0 means random seed
    overlapPred = 4,       -- overlapping edges of center with context
}
In [10]:
load_image = function(filename)
    -- init input_ctx tensor out output_ctx tensor

    inputSize = 128
    -- image_ctx = torch.Tensor(opt.nc, inputSize, inputSize)
    input_ctx = torch.Tensor(opt.nc, inputSize, inputSize)
    output_ctx = torch.Tensor(opt.nc, inputSize, inputSize)
    
    -- load input image
    im_path = 'dali/' .. filename
    input = image.load(im_path, 3, 'float') -- pixel value in 0..1
    input = image.scale(input, inputSize, inputSize)
    input:mul(2):add(-1) -- pixel value in -1..1
    
    -- copy input image to input_ctx tensor and output_ctx tensor
    input_ctx:copy(input)
    output_ctx:copy(input)
    print('Loaded Image Block: ', input_ctx:size(1)..' x '..input_ctx:size(2) ..' x '..input_ctx:size(3))
    
    -- keep real_center in a separate tensor real_center
    real_center = input[{{},{1 + inputSize/4, inputSize/2 + inputSize/4},{1 + inputSize/4, inputSize/2 + inputSize/4}}]:clone() 
    
    -- fill center region with mean value
    input_ctx[{{1},{1 + inputSize/4 + opt.overlapPred, inputSize/2 + inputSize/4 - opt.overlapPred},{1 + inputSize/4 + opt.overlapPred, inputSize/2 + inputSize/4 - opt.overlapPred}}] = 2*117.0/255.0 - 1.0
    input_ctx[{{2},{1 + inputSize/4 + opt.overlapPred, inputSize/2 + inputSize/4 - opt.overlapPred},{1 + inputSize/4 + opt.overlapPred, inputSize/2 + inputSize/4 - opt.overlapPred}}] = 2*104.0/255.0 - 1.0
    input_ctx[{{3},{1 + inputSize/4 + opt.overlapPred, inputSize/2 + inputSize/4 - opt.overlapPred},{1 + inputSize/4 + opt.overlapPred, inputSize/2 + inputSize/4 - opt.overlapPred}}] = 2*123.0/255.0 - 1.0
    
    return input_ctx
    end

In [4]:
predict = function(im)
    -- run Context-Encoder to inpaint center
    pred_center = net:forward(input_ctx)
    print('Prediction: size: ', pred_center:size(1)..' x '..pred_center:size(2) ..' x '..pred_center:size(3)..' x '..pred_center:size(4))
    print('Prediction: Min, Max, Mean, Stdv: ', pred_center:min(), pred_center:max(), pred_center:mean(), pred_center:std())

    -- paste predicted center in output_ctx tensor
    output_ctx[{{},{1 + inputSize/4 + opt.overlapPred, inputSize/2 + inputSize/4 - opt.overlapPred},{1 + inputSize/4 + opt.overlapPred, inputSize/2 + inputSize/4 - opt.overlapPred}}]:copy(pred_center[{{},{},{1 + opt.overlapPred, inputSize/2 - opt.overlapPred},{1 + opt.overlapPred, inputSize/2 - opt.overlapPred}}])

    -- re-transform scale back to normal
    input_ctx:add(1):mul(0.5)
    output_ctx:add(1):mul(0.5)
    
    return output_ctx
end

im = load_image('imagenet/20-imagenet.png')

net:forward(im)

layer1_activations = net:get(1):get(1).output
layer3_activations = net:get(1):get(3).output
layer6_activations = net:get(1):get(6).output
layer9_activations = net:get(1):get(9).output
layer12_activations = net:get(1):get(12).output
layer15_activations = net:get(1):get(15).output
decoder4_activations = net:get(4).output
decoder7_activations = net:get(7).output
decoder10_activations = net:get(10).output
decoder13_activations = net:get(13).output
decoder16_activations = net:get(16).output
decoder17_activations = net:get(17).output

for c=1,64 do
    activation1 = layer1_activations[{{c}, {}, {}}]:reshape(64, 64)
    activation3 = layer3_activations[{{1}, {c}, {}, {}}]:reshape(32, 32)

require 'csvigo'

-- load net
net = torch.load('models/inpaintCenter/imagenet_inpaintCenter.t7')

net:apply(function(m) if m.weight then
    m.gradWeight = m.weight:clone():zero(); -- put grad weight to zero
    m.gradBias = m.bias:clone():zero(); end end)
net:evaluate()

In [27]:



    


for key, db in pairs(dbs) do
    name = db.name
    num = db.num
    print(name, num)
    for i=1,num do
        filename = name .. '/' .. i .. '-' .. name .. '.png'
        im = load_image(filename)
        net:forward(im)
        features = net:get(1):get(15).output:reshape(4000)
        csvigo.save{path='features/' .. name .. '/' .. i .. '-' .. name .. '.csv', data={features:storage():totable()}, mode='raw', header=False}
    end
end

In [36]:



    


filename_to_ids = {}

id=0
for key, db in pairs(dbs) do
    name = db.name
    num = db.num
    for i=1,num do
        filename_to_ids[i .. '-' .. name] = id
        id = id+1
    end
end

ids_to_filename = {}

id=0
for key, db in pairs(dbs) do
    name = db.name
    num = db.num
    for i=1,num do
        ids_to_filename[id] = i .. '-' .. name
        id = id+1
    end
end

require 'csvigo';
require 'image';
require 'nn';

torch.setdefaulttensortype('torch.FloatTensor')
net = torch.load('models/inpaintCenter/imagenet_inpaintCenter.t7')

net:apply(function(m) if m.weight then
    m.gradWeight = m.weight:clone():zero(); -- put grad weight to zero
    m.gradBias = m.bias:clone():zero(); end end)
net:evaluate()

num_images = 2113

for i=1,num_images do

im = load_image(i .. '_im.png')

net:forward(im)
    
features = net:get(1):get(15).output:reshape(4000)
csvigo.save{path='classifier/features/' .. i .. '.csv', data={features:storage():totable()}, mode='raw', header=False}
    
end

require 'csvigo';
require 'image';
require 'nn';

torch.setdefaulttensortype('torch.FloatTensor')
net = torch.load('models/inpaintCenter/imagenet_inpaintCenter.t7')

net:apply(function(m) if m.weight then
    m.gradWeight = m.weight:clone():zero(); -- put grad weight to zero
    m.gradBias = m.bias:clone():zero(); end end)
net:evaluate()


for i=1,112 do

im = load_image(i .. '.png')

net:forward(im)
    
features = net:get(1):get(15).output:reshape(4000)
csvigo.save{path='classifier/aeroplanes/' .. i .. '.csv', data={features:storage():totable()}, mode='raw', header=False}
    
end

motorbikes from recvis/assignment2¶












In [9]:



    


require 'csvigo';
require 'image';
require 'nn';

torch.setdefaulttensortype('torch.FloatTensor')
net = torch.load('models/inpaintCenter/imagenet_inpaintCenter.t7')

net:apply(function(m) if m.weight then
    m.gradWeight = m.weight:clone():zero(); -- put grad weight to zero
    m.gradBias = m.bias:clone():zero(); end end)
net:evaluate()


for i=1,120 do

im = load_image(i .. '.png')

net:forward(im)
    
features = net:get(1):get(15).output:reshape(4000)
csvigo.save{path='classifier/motorbikes/' .. i .. '.csv', data={features:storage():totable()}, mode='raw', header=False}
    
end

91-painting from http://www.cat.uab.cat/~joost/painting91.html¶












In [15]:



    


require 'csvigo';
require 'image';
require 'nn';

torch.setdefaulttensortype('torch.FloatTensor')
net = torch.load('models/inpaintCenter/paris_inpaintCenter.t7')

net:apply(function(m) if m.weight then
    m.gradWeight = m.weight:clone():zero(); -- put grad weight to zero
    m.gradBias = m.bias:clone():zero(); end end)
net:evaluate()


for i=1,46 do

im = load_image('SALVADOR_DALI_' .. i .. '.jpg')

net:forward(im)
    
predictions = predict(im)
    
image.save('predict_' .. i .. '.png', predictions)
    
features = net:get(1):get(15).output:reshape(4000)
csvigo.save{path='dali/' .. i .. '.csv', data={features:storage():totable()}, mode='raw', header=False}
    
end
